{"name": "colorpalette", "metadata": {"name": "colorpalette", "version": "0.3.3", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Objects for coloring strings", "upload_time": 1639378343}, "documentation": ["# colorpalette\n\n```{image} http://img.shields.io/pypi/v/colorpalette.svg?style=flat\n:alt: Version_status\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/colorpalette\n```\n\n```{image} http://img.shields.io/badge/docs-latest-brightgreen.svg?style=flat\n:alt: Documentation\n:target: https://colorpalette.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n```\n\n```{image} http://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg?style=flat\n:alt: license\n:target: https://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette/blob/master/LICENSE.txt\n```\n\n```{contents}\n```\n\n## What is colorpalette?\n\ncolorpalette is an object oriented extension of the [ansicolors package](https://pypi.org/project/ansicolors/). It features Color objects that color strings when called.\n\n## Installation\n\nGet the latest version of colorpalette from\n<https://pypi.python.org/pypi/colorpalette/>\n\nIf you have an installation of Python with pip, simple install it with:\n\n> \\$ pip install colorpalette\n\nTo get the git version, run:\n\n> \\$ git clone git://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette\n\n## Documentation\n\ncolorpalette's documentation is available on the web:\n\n> <http://colorpalette.readthedocs.io/>\n\n## Getting started\n\nTo get started, please go to:\n\n> <https://colorpalette.readthedocs.io/en/latest/GettingStarted.html>\n\n## Latest source code\n\nThe latest development version of colorpalette's sources can be obtained at:\n\n> <https://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette>\n\n## Bug reports\n\nTo report bugs, please use the colorpalette's Bug Tracker at:\n\n> <https://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette>\n\n## License information\n\nSee `LICENSE.txt` for information on the terms & conditions for usage\nof this software, and a DISCLAIMER OF ALL WARRANTIES.\n\nAlthough not required by the colorpalette license, if it is convenient for you,\nplease cite colorpalette if used in your work. Please also consider contributing\nany changes you make back, and benefit the community.\n\n## Citation\n\nTo cite colorpalette in publications use:\n\n```\nYoel Cortes-Pena (2018). colorpalette: Objects for coloring strings\nhttps://github.com/yoelcortes/colorpalette\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["Created on Sun Dec 30 18:42:27 2018\n\n@author: yoelr", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "colorpalette.utils", "documentation": ["Created on Thu Aug 15 03:17:08 2019\n\n@author: yoelr", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "colorpalette.utils.view", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "colors", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "names", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "format", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "colorpalette.utils.rgb2hex", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rgb", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "colorpalette.utils.rgb_tint", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rgb", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "percent", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return tinted rgb by given percent."]}, {"name": "colorpalette.utils.rgb_shade", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rbg", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "percent", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return shaded rgb by given percent."]}, {"name": "colorpalette.utils.decode_ansi", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ansi", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return fg, bg, and style from ansi string."]}], "variables": [{"name": "colorpalette.utils.RGBs", "type": null, "doc